==English==
====Etymology====
Latin ''[[ad]]'' + ''[[iurare]]'', "to swear, to give an oath".
===Verb===
'''to adjure''' ''(third-person singular simple present [[adjures]], present participle [[adjuring]], simple past [[adjured]], past participle [[adjured]])


# To issue a formal command, especially in a legal context.
#:''The Wikitionary admin adjured the editor to cease posting silly articles.'' 
#To earnestly appeal or advise.
#:''Wiktionary editors are adjured to provide etymologies.''

